Author-Name:  Cox, Anthony D
Author-Name:  Moschis, George P
Title: 
 When Consumer Behavior Goes Bad: An Investigation of Adolescent Shoplifting.

Journal: Journal of Consumer Research
Pages: 149-59
Issue: 2
Volume: 17
Year: 1990
Month:  September 
Abstract:

 Shoplifting is a troubling and widespread aspect of consumer behavior,
 particularly among adolescents, yet it has attracted little attention from
 consumer researchers. This article reports and interprets findings on the
 pervasiveness of shoplifting among adolescents, the characteristics that
 distinguish adolescent shoplifters from their nonshoplifting peers, and
 adolescents' views regarding the reasons for this behavior. Our findings
 contradict some popular stereotypes concerning the typical shoplifter and
 suggest some rethinking about adolescents' reasons for shoplifting.


